    "Poker where opponents hold private hands.",
    "Mastering these games requires reasoning over uncertain states, planning multiple moves in advance and managing risk.",
    "Thus, while both subgroups require logical reasoning bounded by formal rules, stochastic games pose the additional challenge of decision-making under uncertainty.",
    "Excelling in deterministic games enables pure reliance on deduction and forward search, while stochastic environments also require abilities for probabilistic inference, risk analysis, and reasoning with incomplete information.",
    "Unlike rule-bounded puzzles, rule-less problems rely more on flexible thinking and real-world knowledge to interpret vague situations and infer unobserved details."
